Fortunately, all the problems were saved, but now he needs to find them among other problems.But there are too many problems, to do it manually. His friends' names are "Danil", "Olya", "Slava", "Ann" and "Nikita".Names are case sensitive.InputThe only line contains string from lowercase and uppercase letters and "_" symbols of length, not more than100â€” the name of the problem.OutputPrint "YES", if problem is from this contest, and "NO" otherwise.ExamplesInputAlex_and_broken_contestOutputNOInputNikitaAndStringOutputYESInputDanil_and_OlyaOutputNO

processed.result:
Given a string representing a problem name, determine if it contains exactly one of the following names: "Danil", "Olya", "Slava", "Ann", or "Nikita".

Return "YES" if the problem name contains exactly one of these names, and "NO" otherwise.
Determine if a given string (a problem name) contains exactly one of the following names: "Danil", "Olya", "Slava", "Ann", or "Nikita".  If it does, output "YES"; otherwise, output "NO".
